  V1 <- df$V1[i]
  V2 <- df$V2[i]

  bw_cov <- get_coverage(V1,

}

# Assuming breast_matrix_vst has the genes AR and ER
AR_ER <- breast_matrix_vst %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = 'gene_id') %>%
  gather(key = 'case_id', value = 'counts', -gene_id) %>%
  filter(gene_id %in% c("AR", "ER")) %>% # Select only AR and ER genes
  spread(key = 'gene_id', value = 'counts') # Spread AR and ER into separate columns

# Calculate median values for AR and ER
median_AR <- median(AR_ER$AR, na.rm = TRUE)
median_ER <- median(AR_ER$ER, na.rm = TRUE)
median_GR <- median(AR_ER$GR, na.rm = TRUE)

# Stratify into four groups: AR_high_ER_high, AR_low_ER_low, AR_high_ER_low, AR_low_ER_high
AR_ER$strata <- case_when(
  AR_ER$AR >= median_AR & AR_ER$ER >= median_ER ~ "AR_high_ER_high",
  AR_ER$AR < median_AR & AR_ER$ER < median_ER ~ "AR_low_ER_low",
  AR_ER$AR >= median_AR & AR_ER$ER < median_ER ~ "AR_high_ER_low",
  AR_ER$AR < median_AR & AR_ER$ER >= median_ER ~ "AR_low_ER_high"
)

# Merge with clinical data to add survival information
AR_ER <- merge(AR_ER, coldata_reordered, by.x = 'case_id', by.y = 'ID')

# Fit survival model
surv_fit <- survdiff(Surv(overall_survival) ~ strata, data = AR_ER)
fit <- survfit(Surv(overall_survival) ~ strata, data = AR_ER)

# Plot survival curve using ggsurvplot
ggsurvplot(fit,
           data = AR_ER,
           pval = TRUE,
           risk.table = TRUE)

# Assuming breast_matrix_vst has the genes AR and ER
AR_ER_GR <- breast_matrix_vst %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = 'gene_id') %>%
  gather(key = 'case_id', value = 'counts', -gene_id) %>%
  filter(gene_id %in% c("AR", "ER","GR")) %>% # Select only AR and ER genes
  spread(key = 'gene_id', value = 'counts') # Spread AR and ER into separate columns

# Calculate median values for AR and ER
median_AR <- median(AR_ER_GR$AR, na.rm = TRUE)
median_ER <- median(AR_ER_GR$ER, na.rm = TRUE)
median_GR <- median(AR_ER_GR$GR, na.rm = TRUE)


# Stratify based on combinations of AR, ER, and GR
AR_ER_GR$strata <- case_when(
  AR_ER_GR$AR >= median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER >= median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR >= median_GR ~ "AR_high_ER_high_GR_high",
  AR_ER_GR$AR < median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER < median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR < median_GR ~ "AR_low_ER_low_GR_low",
  AR_ER_GR$AR >= median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER >= median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR < median_GR ~ "AR_high_ER_high_GR_low",
  AR_ER_GR$AR >= median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER < median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR >= median_GR ~ "AR_high_ER_low_GR_high",
  AR_ER_GR$AR >= median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER < median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR < median_GR ~ "AR_high_ER_low_GR_low",
  AR_ER_GR$AR < median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER >= median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR >= median_GR ~ "AR_low_ER_high_GR_high",
  AR_ER_GR$AR < median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER >= median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR < median_GR ~ "AR_low_ER_high_GR_low",
  AR_ER_GR$AR < median_AR & AR_ER_GR$ER < median_ER & AR_ER_GR$GR >= median_GR ~ "AR_low_ER_low_GR_high"
)


# Merge with clinical data to add survival information
AR_ER_GR <- merge(AR_ER_GR, coldata_reordered, by.x = 'case_id', by.y = 'ID')

# Fit survival model

# looking at some variables associated with survival 
#table(clinical_HNSC$vital_status)

# days_to_death, that is the number of days passed from the initial diagnosis to the patient’s death (clearly, this is only relevant for dead patients)
# days_to_last_follow_up that is the number of days passed from the initial diagnosis to the last visit.

# change certain values the way they are encoded
clinical_HNSC$deceased <- ifelse(clinical_HNSC$vital_status == "Alive", FALSE, TRUE)

# create an "overall survival" variable that is equal to days_to_death
# for dead patients, and to days_to_last_follow_up for patients who
# are still alive
clinical_HNSC$overall_survival <- ifelse(clinical_HNSC$vital_status == "Alive",
                                         clinical_HNSC$days_to_last_follow_up,
                                         clinical_HNSC$days_to_death)

setwd("/scratch/project/stseq/Prakrithi/TCGA/")


# Load your coverage matrix
coverage_matrix <- read.csv("Mel/all_cuTARs/coverage_mat.txt", row.names = 1,sep="\t")

# Load gene lengths (in kb)
gene_lengths <- read.csv("cuTAR_lengths.txt", row.names = 1, sep="\t", header=FALSE)

# Calculate total coverage (N) for each sample
total_coverage <- colSums(coverage_matrix)

# Initialize an empty matrix for FPKM
fpkm_matrix <- coverage_matrix

# Calculate FPKM for each gene in each sample
for (i in 1:ncol(fpkm_matrix)) {
  fpkm_matrix[, i] <- (coverage_matrix[, i] * 1e9) / (gene_lengths * total_coverage[i])
}

# Initialize an empty matrix for TPM
tpm_matrix <- fpkm_matrix

# Calculate TPM by normalizing FPKM
for (i in 1:ncol(tpm_matrix)) {
  scaling_factor <- sum(fpkm_matrix[, i])
  tpm_matrix[, i] <- (fpkm_matrix[, i] / scaling_factor) * 1e6
}

# Save the TPM matrix
write.table(tpm_matrix, "Mel/all_cuTARs/tpm_normalized_matrix.txt",sep="\t", quote = FALSE, row.names = TRUE)
